d small exotic mushrooms preferably chanterelle 8 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil 1 medium size red onion sliced thin 4 tablespoons sherry vinegar salt and freshly ground black pepper 2 bunches fresh arugula rinsed dried and stems removed 1 1 2 ounces parmigiano reggiano in thin shavings 1 strip the kernels off the cob and set aside 2 wipe any dirt from chanterelles with damp paper towel and cut any large ones in half or quarters if using shiitake mushrooms remove and discard stems and cut caps in half inch slices if using small cremini quarter them 3 heat six tablespoon oil in large heavy skillet add onion and saute over medium heat until wilted stir in mushrooms increase heat to high and cook mushrooms until softened and moist looking stir in corn and three tablespoons vinegar and simmer mixture for a minute or two season to taste with salt and pepper set aside off heat until ready to serve 4 to serve toss arugula leaves with remaining vinegar and oil arrange on each of six salad plates briefly reheat the corn mixture and spoon over arugula scatter some cheese on each portion and serve yield 6 servings tomato and feta salad total time 20 minutes 2 pounds ripe tomatoes cored and peeled 2 cucumbers peeled 1 3 cup thinly sliced fresh fennel 1 2 pound feta cheese in 3 4 inch chunks 1 3 cup extra virgin olive oil juice of 1 lemon 1 4 cup diced pitted kalamata olives 1 tablespoon drained capers generous pinch hot red pepper flakes freshly ground black pepper 1 4 cup finely minced fresh basil 1 dice tomatoes into three fourth inch pieces put in a bowl quarter cucumbers lengthwise scoop out seeds and slice three fourth inch thick put in bowl with fennel and feta 2 add oil lemon juice olives capers and red and black pepper gently fold all ingredients together 3 allow to marinate about an hour at room temperature add basil toss gently then serve yield 6 servings

